					</li>									</ol>								</li>								<li>									In <a href="2">Part 2</a>,									Darak wanders out of the wilderness to a rural town where he is discovered to much fanfare, which ultimately leads Mav to descend upon the town to kill him.									<ol>										<li>											In <a href="2/1">Episode 1</a>,											Darak wanders out of the wilderness to a rural town, where authorities attempt to apprehend him and, failing to overpower him, call for outside help.										</li>										<li>											In <a href="2/2">Episode 2</a>,											a wizard ranger arrives at the rural town holding young Darak Meij, and tries to establish communication with the feral child until disaster befalls them all.										</li>										<li>											In <a href="2/3">Episode 3</a>,											Mav the Witch-Queen descends upon the rural town seeking to kill the last Meij to slip through her fingers, but is driven back by his surprising furious might.										</li>									</ol>								</li>								<li>									In <a href="3">Part 3</a>,									a reluctant coalition of political powers coalesces around Darak's quest to kill Mav, leading to both of their deaths and the expulsion of wizards from the public sphere.									<ol>										<li>											In <a href="3/1">Episode 1</a>,											a coalition of different political forces, both mundane and magical, begins to form behind Darak's unyeilding quest to kill Mav the Witch-Queen.										</li>										<li>											In <a href="3/2">Episode 2</a>,											Mav is successfully driven out of the continent Darak's quest began on, but the coalition is forced to become global when Darak will not stop pursuing her.										</li>										<li>											In <a href="3/3">Episode 3</a>,											Darak hunts Mav down to the farthest reaches and kills her in a spectacular duel, before being assasinated by mundane forces who've plotted against him all along.										</li>									</ol>								</li>							</ol>						</li>					</ol>				</section><? require $_SERVER['DOCUMENT_ROOT'] . "/includes/footer-global.php" ?>